entry.title: Russian Forces Press Ukrainian Defense in Northeast
entry.content: Moscow is seeking to gain an advantage ahead of the arrival of more powerful weapons in Ukraine from the West.

entry.title: Rescue Teams Race to Find Earthquake Survivors in Turkey, Syria
entry.content: The death toll from the earthquakes that struck Turkey and Syria rose past 11,700 and is expected to continue climbing, as freezing temperatures continued to complicate humanitarian efforts.

entry.title: Russia Throws Soldiers Into Firing Line to Gain Inches
entry.content: Moscow has shown scant regard for the lives of its conscripts, but the battle for Bakhmut is also costly for Ukrainian defenders.
